  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Citizens Working Together To Combat Corruption within Ghana Police Service</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">An increase in citizens&#x2019; demand for accountability of the Ghana Police Service and reporting of corruption and officer misconduct. 
Key concerns and issues relating to corruption raised and increase demand for accountability, especially in 3 communities. 
Better informed  citizenry on corruption, understanding of their rights promoted on GPW  and social media,
Improved public perception and confidence in GPS anti-corruption measures and justice for victims of officer misconduct</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Thirteen (13) Ghana Police Watch Television Programmes that will provide a platform for citizens to engage with GPS on issues related to anti &#x2013; corruption.
Led by Ghana Anti - Corruption Coalition from the second year, CSN and partners will organize the Joint GPS and civil society engagements, which will take the form of &#x2018;community durbars&#x2019; and involve a broad range of citizens, as well as key local stakeholders including traditional leaders, religious leaders, women groups, Queen mothers, professional and artisan associations, drivers unions and others</narrative>
  </description>
